byline.contributor: Zeinab Mohammed Salih reported from El Fasher, and Jeffrey Gettleman from Nairobi, Kenya.
byline.original: By ZEINAB MOHAMMED SALIH and JEFFREY GETTLEMAN

abstract: Low turnout mars referendum on whether Darfur should be one semiautonomous state or remain broken up in five separate pieces; public remains skeptical of political process.
lead_paragraph: The referendum on whether the Sudanese region should remain as five semiautonomous states or be made into one has been dismissed by some as a meaningless administrative exercise.

headline.main: Light Turnout for Vote in Darfur on Region’s Future
headline.print_headline: Light Turnout for Vote on Future of Darfur

snippet: The referendum on whether the Sudanese region should remain as five semiautonomous states or be made into one has been dismissed by some as a meaningless administrative exercise.
